ECR(Elastic container registry)
ECS(Elastic container service)
Why ECR?
it is nothing like docker hub account to store image but it is from AWS SERVICE PROVIDER
HOW CAN I STORE THE IMAGES?
We have to create docker image in EC2
after we have to create iam role to give permissions to EC2
->IAM ROLE->AWS serviec->ec2->select ecr full and ecs full permissions-> save it
->ec2->Actions->security->modify role and selecte these create role
After we have to create ecr registry?
-> ecr>create registry->give reg name-> create
->open that registred ecr-> click view commands
it will commands like these
COm1: aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin 082569478325.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
note:com1 will work after creating iam role and attach 
com2: docker build -t shasi .
com3: docker tag shasi:latest 082569478325.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/shasi:latest
com4: docker push 082569478325.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/shasi:latest
Now you can check that registry image was stored or not.
